Sorry to bare my soul on this app but today was one of those moments in life when you realize you’ve gotten everything you used to pray for. A couple of years ago I used to get off work and cry. I wanted to be a mom and a wife and I felt that it would never happen for me. I stayed up at night praying that one day I’d have my little family. I wanted to have my Journalism career and then get off work and go home to my people. Today was really the first moment I finally took a second to look around and realize I’m living that vision. Today I walked my daughter around the news studio and she even had her debut on the desk. Anchor in the making!

365 days difference. That second picture was my first day back at the gym after getting cleared by the doctor. I remember taking that picture in the locker room and feeling awful. All of the work I put in before getting pregnant and delivering seemed to be completely gone. I didn’t recognize myself. I felt out of place in the gym once again and the journey to where I wanted to be seemed like a long, daunting road…almost impossible. But I kept on. I cried, I got mad, I had days of no motivation, I had days I felt I was making no progress but I kept on. And today I look back on that journey and feel so proud of myself. Proud that I didn’t give up. I am stronger in the gym today than I was before I became a mom, and that’s mind blowing to me. Becoming a mom gave me a strength I didn’t know I had. I know I’ve got many followers on here who are going through this same journey and today if you find yourself looking down that long road feeling like it just might be impossible… please keep going. Keep showing up for yourself. You’re going to look back a year from now and be blown away by what you’ve accomplished. To all my mamas out there, you’re absolutely incredible, we made a life! Cheers to that.

POV: You’re a PA and you watch me stumble over my words on a Tuesday morning. Sometimes your brain and your tongue live on different planets, and that’s just life folks. One day you’re on fire and the next you struggle saying simple English words. 

To my fellow newsies who can relate, let’s keep on truckin.

I reached a point in my life where the little things are the most special. Enjoying a cup of coffee early in the morning, sitting next to my plants on the patio while my baby sleeps peacefully in her crib has become the feeling I measure everything else to. I sincerely hope with my entire heart that you find what fills your soul. And on your search, I hope you know it doesn’t have to be grand. It can be small, quiet, simple, soft.
